items.title: Q&A: Betts touches all the bases
items.summary: At the age of 24, Red Sox right fielder Mookie Betts is three weeks from completing his third full season and has established himself as one of the most electrifying players in the game. In a recent sitdown at Fenway Park with MLB.com, discussed a number of different topics.

items.title: Marlins Park OK after Hurricane Irma
items.summary: Marlins Park withstood the wrath of Hurricane Irma on Sunday, sustaining minor roof damage, but the building did not experience any flooding or water damage, the Marlins said in a statement. But whether the Marlins play host to the Brewers on Friday still has not been determined.
